  "review_text": "There were only five books this month, and for the third month running, the weighted average was only [SPAN: severity=error; fontsize=large; fonttype=bold; text=x.xx].\n\nIt is <i>not</i> a good beginning of 1963 for Marvel, particularly when the <i>best book of the month</i> was the Ant-Man/Wasp pairing, which is a true testament to how awful the <i>rest</i> of the offerings were.&nbsp; <i>Tales to Abolish</i> being the best Marvel had to offer this month?&nbsp; That's a shocker!\n\n\n[DEVNOTE: *** SUMMARY_BEGIN ***\n*** THIS MONTH ***5 graded stories over 5 issues...TOTAL WEIGHT: 3.25 grade character issue   weight 4.5   ant       TTA #44 0.75 3.5   thor      JIM #92 0.50 3.5   ff        FF #15  1.00 2.0   torch     ST #109 0.50 2.0   iron      TOS #42 0.503.27*** LAST MONTH ***7 graded stories over 6 issues...TOTAL WEIGHT: 4 grade character issue   weight 8.0   asm       ASM #2  0.5 5.5   asm       ASM #2  0.5 3.0   thor      JIM #91 0.5 2.0   ant       TTA #43 0.5 2.0   torch     ST #108 0.5 1.5   ff        FF #14  1.0 1.0   iron      TOS #41 0.53.06\n*** SUMMARY_END ***]",
  "letters_page": "[HANG0] * Obviously the top highlight of the month was the introduction of the Wasp, who will of course become a founding member of the Avengers.\n[HANG0] * Introduction of the Mad Thinker and his Android\n[HANG0] * And we got a bit more than just the  passing glimpse into the goings-on in Asgard.\n\n\n[DEVNOTE: *** INTRODUCTION_BEGIN ***\nJanet Van Dyne | Milestone: (first)\nNotes | first | villain | Creature from Kosmos\nAwesome Android | villain | Milestone: (first)\nMad Thinker | villain | Milestone: (first)\nNotes | first | villain | Sorcerer (Dorian Murdstone)\nNotes | first | villain | Red Guardian\n*** INTRODUCTION_END ***]\n[DEVNOTE: *** HIGHLIGHTS_BEGIN ***]\n[HANG0] * Loki's latest scheme is a clever premise stretched thin, chained to a single plot trick.\n[HANG0] * Hank Pym gains a tragic backstory and a partner in record time -- hello, Wasp.\n[HANG0] * FIXME - write something\n[HANG0] * FIXME - write something\n[HANG0] * FIXME - write something\n[DEVNOTE: *** HIGHLIGHTS_END ***]",
  "ownership": "[HANG0] * Thor messes with something radioactive\n[HANG0] * The guy with the ridiculous noggin returns to plague Ant-Man and his new partner, the Wasp\n[HANG9] * Spider-Man is back to face a new menace with four extra arms\n[HANG0] * Dr. Doom reappears, and the FF need the Ant-Man's help\n[HANG0] * Two frightful old enemies of the Human Torch join forces\n[HANG0] * Iron Man goes <i>way </i>down under\n[HANG0] * and who is this weird Dr. Strange fellow?\n[BR] He looks <i>nothing</i> like the Dr. Strange who just recently fought Iron Man last month.\n[BR] Does he have a future?"
}